                            <h3>Privacy Policy</h3>
                            <p align="justify">Footwear Design & Development Institute (FDDI) is committed to respecting your privacy. This statement applies with respect to information we collect from http://www.fddiindia.com and any other sites on the World Wide Web owned and/or operated by Footwear Design & Development Institute (FDDI), Noida. This statement is part of our Terms of Use and is subject to all of its terms. Below is information regarding the commitment of FDDI to protect the personal data of its website visitors.</p>
                            <p align="justify">The term “personal data” includes any information that enables you to be identified, such as your name, physical address, e-mail address and phone number.</p>
                            <h5>Nature Of The Data Collected And Purpose Of The Data Processing</h5>
                            <p align="justify">When you access this Web site, FDDI collects the IP address of the computer you are using to browse the site. If this address is a “static” or fixed IP address, FDDI could in certain circumstances theoretically be able to identify you, and therefore, this type of information could be considered personal data. However, FDDI only collects this type of information to compile usage statistics on an anonymous basis; FDDI does not collect IP address data to identify you.</p>
                            <p align="justify">Apart from your IP address, no personal data is transmitted when accessing this Web site. Unless you submit personal data about yourself by filling in a form on the Web site or by sending us an e-mail, we will not maintain any other personal data as a result of your access and usage of the site.</p>
                            <p align="justify">The Web site invites you to register with us on-line, by providing your personal information. No information pertaining to your Credit Card is captured and/or maintained by FDDI. All such information are directly captured by Payment Gateway website only that is certified and secure.</p>
                            <p align="justify">We use the information you submit by registering to send you information by post, Online Application Form or e-mail. You may request to cease receiving such information at any time following registration. You may request to be removed from our e-mail list by sending an email to contact@fddiindia.com with the word “UNSUBSCRIBE” in the email subject line or by following the unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of the email. You may request to be removed from our postal mailing list by sending an e-mail message to contact@fddiindia.com or by sending a letter to:</p>
                            <br>
                            <p align="justify">
                                Attn: Information Technology Service Center (ITSC)<br>
                                Footwear Design & Development Institute (FDDI)<br>
								A-10/A, Sector-24, NOIDA, Gautam Budh Nagar,<br>
                                Uttar Pradesh - 201301, INDIA
                            </p>
                            <p align="justify">The site may also require you to register to enjoy certain services provided through the site, such as on-line support or on-line education. The information provided in the context of registering for these services is collected to respond to your inquiry, process an order, to provide you with access to specific account information or to enable us to provide you the aforementioned on-line services securely through password protection.</p>
                            <p align="justify">In addition, in order to better understand the needs of the visitors of this Web site and to adapt the Web site to these needs, we occasionally conduct on-line surveys. Participation in these surveys is optional. The data collected through these surveys is used for statistical analysis of visitor, FDDI courses & programs or services category assessments and for direct marketing purposes.</p>
                            <h5>Disclosure Of Personal Data</h5>
                            <p align="justify">Unless we tell you otherwise, we do not sell or rent your personal data to any third parties. When involved in a joint marketing partnership, FDDI may share information which you have submitted to us with the partner company which is subject to applicable non-disclosure obligations. The information that you have submitted while filling the Application Form online, will be kept secure at FDDI’s secure hosted servers. The complete data flow of entire process is as follows:</p>
                            <h5>Use Of “Cookies”</h5>
                            <p align="justify">Certain section on this Web site sends “cookies” to your computer to better serve you with more tailored information when you return to the website. A cookie is a small element of data that can be sent by our web site to your browser and stored on your hard drive, not on FDDI's web site. Cookies do not collect information about visitors. Unless you input your Personal Data onto our website you cannot be identified and remain anonymous. You can set most browsers to tell you when you are sent a cookie and to refuse to receive it.</p>
                            <p align="justify">Disclosure Your Data To Other Entities, Such As A Group Under FDDI Flagship And To Third Parties</p>
                            <p align="justify">FDDI may disclose your personal data to other entities within its flagship and to third parties to the extent that such disclosure is not incompatible with the purposes for which the personal data is collected as mentioned above.</p>
                            <p align="justify">In addition, FDDI may disclose your personal data to other entities within its association or flagship belonging to FDDI or third parties around the world.</p>
                            <h5>Security Of Your Data</h5>
                            <p align="justify">FDDI takes all reasonable precautions to adequately prevent others from freely accessing the information you provide or that we compile. As you are no doubt aware, however, despite these precautions, zealous hackers may wrongfully gain access to this information. Although such unauthorized access is unlikely, we feel obligated to inform you of the risk and advise you that FDDI is not liable for any damages caused by such unauthorized access. However to minimize any such risk to our visitors, FDDI encrypts all transactions between you and FDDI Website using 128 bit encryption technology. All personal information we obtain from you will be held securely on our secure hosted servers and will not stored on any public servers, directly accessible from the Internet.</p>
                            <h5>Third Party Sites</h5>
                            <p align="justify">This policy only addresses our activities from our servers. Other sites (including those that we link to within an advertisement banner or otherwise, and third party sites or services which we cobrand) may have their own policies, which we do not control, and thus are not addressed by this policy.</p>
                            <h5>Your Right To Access, Correction, And Erasure</h5>
